==English==
===Etymology===
{{L.}} ''quaerere'': to ask; to seek
===Transitive Verb===
#To question. Used to signify doubt or suggest investigation.
*'''Quaere:''' Did John actually say that?
===Noun===
#Archaic: A question.
==Latin==
Imperitive form of [[quaerere]]
